The paper deals with the classification of EEG signals using advanced feature extraction techniques and machine learning algorithms. This falls under the domain of neural engineering (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of EEG signals for brain-computer interface (BCI) also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of brain activity, which falls under the domain of computational biology (cs.BIO).
